<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>20762</anchor> <rss>karlcrary.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>karlcrary</addr>  <route>karlcrary.xml</route>   <title>Karl Crary</title> <meta name="institution">Carnegie Mellon University</meta><meta name="position">Professor</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>20763</anchor> <rss>jms-009L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Letter</taxon> <addr>jms-009L</addr>  <route>jms-009L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>22</day></date> <authors><author><link href="karlcrary.xml" type="local">Karl Crary</link></author> </authors> <title>Edmund M. Clarke Dissertation Award</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Dear friends,</p><p>I am delighted to announce that <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jonathan Sterling">Jonathan Sterling</link> has been selected as the winner of the 2022 Edmund M. Clarke Dissertation Award in CSD for his thesis:</p><p><link href="sterling-2021-thesis.xml" type="local" title="First Steps in Synthetic Tait Computability">First Steps in Synthetic Tait Computability</link>, October 2021</p><p><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jonathan">Jonathan</link>’s PhD research was advised by <link href="robertharper.xml" type="local" title="Robert Harper">Robert Harper</link>.</p><p>This award, endowed by a generous contribution from Professor Ed Clarke and his wife Martha, is given annually to an outstanding dissertation in the Computer Science Department.</p><p>Congratulations <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jonathan">Jonathan</link>!</p></mainmatter> </tree></contributions> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>20764</anchor> <rss>2023-09-22.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-09-22</addr>  <route>2023-09-22.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>22</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-09-22</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Today I am working on releasing <link href="jms-007M.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.4">Forester 2.4</link> to <link href="https://github.com/ocaml/opam-repository/pull/24505" type="external">opam</link>.</p><p><link href="karlcrary.xml" type="local" title="Karl Crary">Karl Crary</link> announced that I won the <link href="jms-009J.xml" type="local" title="2022 Ed Clarke Dissertation Award">2022 Ed Clarke Dissertation Award</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>